body: Awesome thanks a lot for the quick reply @snnn. Your code does not segfault for me!

I know it's very confusing: we have two different APIs for init a CUDA Execution Provider:

1. OrtSessionOptionsAppendExecutionProvider_CUDA. A global function. Deprecated.
2. g_ort->SessionOptionsAppendExecutionProvider_CUDA. A function pointer

Both of them have two parameters. But the second parameter of the first one is an integer, which accepts 0. The second parameter of the second function expects a data pointer.
@snnn oh thanks a lot for this extra explanation. Now I get it.

issue.title: Missing header in 1.9.0 win x64 GPU release

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
**Describe the bug**
The latest release fails to compile the C++ inference samples.
The header file `cuda_provider_factor.h` is reported as missing.
Adding it manually then triggers a missing include `core/framework/provider_options.h` in `cuda_provider_factor.h`
Replacing it with `provider_options.h` finally allow it to compile.


**Urgency**
None

**System information**
- Win10
- binary
- 1.9.0

**To Reproduce**
- Download 1.9.0 binaries
- Clone inference example repo: https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime-inference-examples
- Attempt to compile with GPU support enabled

**Expected behavior**
Examples compiling

**Additional context**
Related to https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/9148

issue.title: Change Onnxruntime version to 1.9.0 and then encounter Ort::Session session BUG .

labels.name: ep:CUDA
labels.description: issues related to the CUDA execution provider

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
I run the same piece of code and use the same model, it can succeed before upgrading the Onnxruntime version, but in order to upgrade CUDA, I updated the version to 1.9.0 and encountered a bug. It is now clear that the bug originated from the following sentence:


`Ort::Env env(ORT_LOGGING_LEVEL_WARNING, "test");`
`Ort::SessionOptions session_options;`
`OrtSessionOptionsAppendExecutionProvider_CUDA(session_options, 0);`
`wchar_t *path = L"test.onnx";`
`Ort::Session session(env, path, session_options);`


In fact, commenting out the sentence calling CUDA `OrtSessionOptionsAppendExecutionProvider_CUDA(session_options, 0); ` will also report this error.


------------------------------------

Former Successful Version:
RTX2070
CUDA:10.0
Cudnn:7.5
[Onnxruntime:1.1.2-gpu](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/releases/tag/v1.1.2)


-------------------------------------
Latest Error Version:
RTX2070
CUDA:11.4
Cudnn:8.2
[Onnxruntime:1.9.0-gpu](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/releases/tag/v1.9.1)


**System information**
- OS Platform and Distribution (Windows 10):
- Visual Studio version (2015):

Which friend can answer for me?
